  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (c0667c5 2022-05-18T00:11:45.21540785Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test (but probably applies to others)\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI'm trying to parse the output for some 3rd party tooling.\r\nWhen running `forge test --json`, there's a lot of noise around the actual json content, so I need to pipe it into other commands in other to filter out the noise\r\n\r\nCurrently trying to run `forge test --json | head -n 2 | tail -n 1`. This should give me the 2nd line of output, which should consistently match the json\r\n\r\nHowever, this triggers the following error:\r\n```\r\n‚ùØ forge test --match-path test/AnotherContract.t.sol --match-contract ContractTest --json | head -n 1                                                                       \r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped                                                 \r\nThe application panicked (crashed).                                                   \r\nMessage:  failed printing to stdout: Broken pipe (os error 32)                        \r\nLocation: library/std/src/io/stdio.rs:1164                                            \r\n                                                                                      \r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.      \r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.                              \r\nzsh: IOT instruction (core dumped)  forge test --match-path test/AnotherContract.t.sol --match-contract  --json |                                                           \r\nzsh: done                           head -n 1    \r\n```",
