    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "By noisy I meant that it can't be directly piped to other tooling that expects JSON input (e.g.: the VS Code test runner I was setting up)\r\n\r\nThe first line will always be the \"No files changed. Compilation skipped\"\r\nAnd in case of test failures, there's other output afterwards as well if I recall correctly (can't check right now, at the airport)\r\n\r\nI considered seeing if it was trivial to suppress that output in some way (maybe using the existing `TermSettings`). But for now I just went with piping the output to `sed` for filtering\r\n\r\nWhich is where this error first showed up. Using tail to get only the first N lines was my first solution, but that closes stdout prematurely and leads to a panick",
